## [2026-04-26, UTC] Multi-CLI full-codebase review iter-7 (v0.7.5) ƒ?" first broader sweep

**Action:** Ran Codex (gpt-5.4 xhigh) + Opus 4.7 (1M) full-codebase review against `main` HEAD `c2f8db3` (v0.7.4). Gemini quota-exhausted (5th iter in a row, 17h48m reset). Iter-1ƒ?"6 had focused on the `CommandTransaction` atomicity chain; iter-7 is the first sweep of the rest of the engine surface (entity-manager, component-store, spatial-grid, event-bus, queue, resource-store, pathfinding, BT, noise, cellular, serializer, client-adapter, render-adapter, occupancy-grid, visibility-map, path-service, history-recorder, scenario-runner, world-debugger, map-gen, world-internal). Findings synthesized at `docs/reviews/full/2026-04-26/7/REVIEW.md`: 1 High, 3 Medium, 3 Low, no Critical, no regressions from v0.7.4 followups.

**Code review breakdown by AI provider and theme:**

- **Codex:** 1 High (`World.deserialize` accepts dead/non-integer entity IDs in components+resources), 2 Medium (EventBus listener-mutates-payload, ClientAdapter mapping race after safeSend failure), 1 Low (`octaveNoise2D` parameter validation).
- **Opus:** 1 Medium (api-reference snapshot v4ƒ+'v5 doc drift), 2 Low (component-store revert-to-baseline diff bloat, deserialize tick-validation hoist).
- **Gemini:** UNREACHABLE (`429 QUOTA_EXHAUSTED`).
- **Coverage signal:** Zero overlap between Codex and Opus findings ƒ?" they audited disjoint subsystems and each found what the other missed. The two-perspective review continues to be a stronger signal than any single reviewer.

**Fixes shipped (one commit, v0.7.5):**

- **H1 (Codex):** snapshot-boundary entity-id validation. Before any loader runs, every `[id, _]` pair in `snapshot.components[*]`, `snapshot.resources.pools[*]`, `snapshot.resources.production[*]`, `snapshot.resources.consumption[*]`, and every `from`/`to` on `snapshot.resources.transfers[*]` is checked against (i) `Number.isInteger(id) && id >= 0` and (ii) `world.entityManager.isAlive(id)`. Throws on violation. Mirrors the v0.6.2 `snapshot.tick` validation precedent and the existing tags/metadata validation. The bug class: dead-entity rows would re-populate stores and become queryable through `world.grid` / `queryInRadius`; negative/fractional IDs would silently mismatch `_size` vs iteration. 6 new regression tests in `tests/serializer.test.ts`.
- **M1 (Codex):** `EventBus.emit` deep-clones `data` once for the buffer and once per listener. Prior behavior pushed the caller's reference into the buffer and passed the same reference to every listener ƒ?" a listener that mutated `data` corrupted buffered history visible to `getEvents()` and to later listeners; a listener that made `data` circular caused later `getEvents()` calls to throw. The fix mirrors the iter-6 atomicity discipline: engine-owned state must be structurally isolated from external callbacks. `getEvents()` still clones on read for caller-side defense. Cost: N+1 clones per emit (acceptable; emit-time `assertJsonCompatible` already ensures the payload is JSON-serializable). 3 new regression tests.
- **M2 (Codex):** `ClientAdapter.handleMessage` now gates the `clientCommandIds.set(result.sequence, id)` on the boolean return of `safeSend`. Prior behavior unconditionally set the mapping after the send, even when `safeSend` had already disconnected and cleared the per-client map on transport failure ƒ?" leaving either a leaked map entry (no reconnect) or causing the next session to receive `commandExecuted` / `commandFailed` against an unknown sequence. 1 new regression test.
- **M3 (Opus):** `docs/api-reference.md` ƒ?" replaced two stale `(snapshot v4)` parenthetical labels in the "World State" and "Tags & Metadata" sections with `(snapshot v5)`. Current `SCHEMA_VERSION` is 5; the labels diverged from runtime.
- **L1 (Codex):** `octaveNoise2D` now throws `RangeError` on `octaves < 1` or non-integer, `persistence < 0` or non-finite, `lacunarity <= 0` or non-finite. Prior behavior: `octaves = 0` returned NaN; non-finite parameters propagated as Infinity / NaN through downstream map-gen. `api-reference.md` updated with explicit constraint columns. 6 new regression tests.
- **L2 (Opus):** `ComponentStore` semantic-mode `set` now `dirtySet.delete(entityId)` and `removedSet.delete(entityId)` when the new value matches the baseline. Prior behavior: pattern `set(A) ƒ+' clearDirty ƒ+' set(B) ƒ+' set(A)` left the entity in `dirtySet` even though the final value matched the baseline, so `getDirty()` emitted a redundant entry ƒ?" diff bandwidth waste, no incorrect end state. 1 new regression test.
- **L3 (Opus):** Hoisted the `snapshot.tick` validation block in `World.deserialize` to the top of the method (right after the version check), above all loaders and `rebuildSpatialIndex`. Cheap constant-time check now fails fast before any O(N) work runs on a snapshot that will be rejected. The `tags` / `metadata` `assertEntityIdAlive` block now sits inline with the new components / resources entity-id validation, all driven through a shared `assertEntityIdAlive` closure for consistency.

**Reasoning:**

- **Single-commit shipment:** Per AGENTS.md "One version bump per coherent shipped change" ƒ?" these 7 fixes are one coherent response to one review pass. Bundled as v0.7.5 rather than 4ƒ?"6 micro-bumps to keep the changelog readable. Iter-1ƒ?"6 used both styles; this iter is the simpler "iter-2 batch 5"-equivalent style.
- **H1 is the largest fix:** the deserialize boundary is the most consequential gap ƒ?" `tick` was already validated (v0.6.2), tags/metadata IDs were already validated (existing code), but components/resources slipped through. Closing them brings the whole snapshot loader under the same fail-fast contract.
- **M1 cost analysis:** Deep-cloning per listener is N+1 clones per emit. The cost matters only on event-heavy systems with many listeners; the alternative (sharing a single clone) lets listener mutations leak between subscribers, which violates the iter-6 atomicity contract. Chose correctness over micro-perf; the JSON-clone path is already fast on V8 for plain objects.

**Iter-7 verification status:** This iter's fixes have NOT been re-reviewed by Codex/Opus yet ƒ?" that's iter-8 (the convergence check). The iter-7 review prompt explicitly said "do not re-flag deferred items from iter-1ƒ?"6"; iter-8 will verify these fixes landed cleanly and check for any introduced regressions.

**Result:** 627 tests pass (up from 608). Typecheck, lint, build clean.

