docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:49:Per AGENTS.md "tests-first": added 7 new tests under three new 
`describe` blocks (`precondition read-only enforcement`, `poisoned-world warning`, `terminal status error messages`) 
before touching `src/`, plus updated the existing `emit at commit-time validates JSON-compat` test to match the new 
buffer-time semantics.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:66:- **H2 - Layer sparsity hole (Codex + Gemini High, two-reviewer 
consensus):** `setCell` / `setAt` / `fill` now compare incoming value against `defaultValue` and `cells.delete(idx)` 
on match (instead of storing a marker entry). `fill(defaultValue)` short-circuits to `cells.clear()`. The in-memory 
map and the `getState` output now stay in sync without a round-trip. Equality test: strict `===` for primitive `T`, 
`jsonFingerprint` comparison for object `T`.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:69:- **M4 - `Layer.fromState` double-validate (Opus Medium):** 
`assertJsonCompatible(value)` was being called explicitly per cell, then `jsonFingerprint(value)` was called, and 
`jsonFingerprint`'s implementation calls `assertJsonCompatible` itself - paying validation twice. Removed the explicit 
call. `fromState` now validates each value once.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:71:- **Bonus** `forEachReadOnly(cb)` - added as the explicit 
zero-allocation traversal path for object `T` consumers who own the no-mutate discipline. Documented in api-reference. 
Existing `forEach` keeps its safe-clone semantics.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:73:**Reasoning:** Picked H2+H4+L5+M4+M5 as a coherent Layer overhaul 
because all five touch the same file (`src/layer.ts`) and the same defensive-copy contract surface. Strip-at-write 
(H2) and primitive fast-path (H4) interact: the new `matchesDefault(value)` helper uses the cached `_isPrimitive` flag 
to pick `===` vs `jsonFingerprint`. Splitting them into separate commits would have meant carrying intermediate `if 
(_isPrimitive)` branching in two adjacent commits.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:137:- **Opus 4.7 (1M):** 1 iter-1 regression (R1 same, with detailed 
enumeration of missing/spurious entries and full source-of-truth list) + 1 High (`Layer.forEachReadOnly` null bug, 
same as Gemini) + 1 Medium (writer double-validate) + 3 Low (getState dead fingerprint, stale test name, residual `as 
any` cast on emit dispatch). Theme: defensive enforcement gaps + dead-code from the H2 strip-at-write change.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:151:- **M_NEW1 + M_NEW2 (Opus + Gemini Medium):** 
`Layer.setCell`/`setAt`/`fill` and `Layer.fromState` were paying double JSON-compat validation per write/load - 
`assertJsonCompatible(value)` explicit + `jsonFingerprint(value)` (which calls `assertJsonCompatible` internally per 
`json.ts:60`). Fix: branch on `_defaultIsPrimitive`. For primitive-default layers, skip `jsonFingerprint` (use direct 
`===` for default-equality) and validate explicitly via `assertJsonCompatible`. For object-default layers, use 
`jsonFingerprint` and rely on its internal validation. Each value pays exactly one validation walk per boundary.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:157:- **L_NEW3 (Opus Low):** `Layer.getState()` had a defensive `if 
(jsonFingerprint(value) === this._defaultFingerprint) continue;` filter. Post-H2 strip-at-write, every public path 
that inserts strips defaults - and `cells` is `private`, so no public bypass exists. Dead code. Removed.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:184:- **Opus 4.7 (1M):** verified iter-2 fixes clean, reached the same 
root-cause findings as Codex via different framing - N1 noted `warnIfPoisoned` was a denylist hole and N3 noted the 
property-based test does not cross-check against World - plus 1 Low doc drift (`api-reference.md:3454` still claims 
