docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:194:- **Meta-test (Codex L_REG2 + Opus N3):** added a property-based 
meta-test that cross-checks `FORBIDDEN_PRECONDITION_METHODS` against `Object.getOwnPropertyNames(World.prototype)`. 
Filters known read-only + TypeScript-private methods via an explicit allowlist. Future World method additions that 
aren't classified fail the suite. Also asserts no entries in the FORBIDDEN array reference non-existent World methods. 
This is exactly the missing safety net that allowed R2_REG1 (and the original R1) to slip past existing tests.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-26.md:239:- **Codex (gpt-5.4, xhigh):** verified iter-4 test fix correct; 
